@startuml
' @id(SEQ-RENDER-DIFF-SVG)
' @ref(USE-DIFF-DIAGRAM)
' @ref(DOM-RENDER-ENGINE)
'
' Current-side flow as implemented: the `mdd render` mdd-cli subcommand
' (Commands::Render) builds a RenderSelection and calls the single
' mdd_render::render_selection engine, which enumerates the tree set via
' mdd_core Project (RenderTree) and writes each Project::rendered_mirror_path.
'
' @desc(SEQ-RENDER-DIFF-SVG, "As-built: `mdd render` (Commands::Render) resolves RenderSelection (All / Trees(--only) / Paths) and calls render_selection, which pulls sources from Project::all_render_sources or render_sources (RenderTree::ALL — models, cycle diffs, OCL, whole-map, deploy, review-diff), synthesizes OCL first, pipes each through PlantUmlCommand, and writes Project::rendered_mirror_path; per-file failures become diagnostics (non-zero exit) instead of aborting. render_cycle_diffs/render_project/render_ocl_diagrams are thin wrappers. The /mdd-render skill adds only fuzzy subset intake + triage.")
title Rasterize the renderable trees via `mdd render` (current)

actor "Developer / CI" as Dev
participant "/mdd-cycle close\nor /mdd-render skill\n(thin wrapper)" as Trigger
participant "mdd render\n(mdd-cli Commands::Render)" as Cli
participant "Project (RenderTree)\nall_render_sources / render_sources" as Core
participant "render_selection\n(mdd-render engine)\n+ PlantUmlCommand" as Rend
database ".mdd/{models,cycles,constraints,\nmap,deploy,rendered/review}/**" as Store
database ".mdd/rendered/**\n(rendered_mirror_path)" as Out

Dev -> Trigger : close cycle N  /  /mdd-render [fuzzy subset?]
note right of Trigger
  Skill judgment only: "just the deploy diagrams"
  -> `mdd render --only deploy`. It shells to the
  binary; no hand-run PlantUML.
end note
Trigger -> Cli : `mdd render` (or --only <trees> / paths)
Cli -> Cli : build RenderSelection\n(All / Trees / Paths)
Cli -> Rend : render_selection(project, &selection)
Rend -> Core : all_render_sources() / render_sources(tree)
Core --> Rend : sorted (tree, PathBuf) — single source
opt no sources matched
  Rend --> Cli : empty RenderReport (not an error)
end
loop each source file
  Rend -> Store : read source
  alt OCL source
    Rend -> Rend : synthesize_ocl_puml first
  end
  Rend -> Rend : out = Project::rendered_mirror_path(src)\n(review diffs kept in place)
  alt render ok
    Rend -> Out : PlantUmlCommand -tsvg -pipe -> write mirror
  else plantuml failure
    Rend -> Rend : push diagnostic (continue)
  end
end
Rend --> Cli : RenderReport { rendered, diagnostics }
Cli --> Trigger : print rendered + diagnostics; exit 1 if any diagnostic
opt diagnostics present
  Trigger -> Dev : triage + fix suggestion (skill judgment)
end
Trigger --> Dev : cycle N closed / subset rendered; SVGs ready for the viewer

note over Out
  Every tree's output is Project::rendered_mirror_path
  of its source (OCL-RENDER-PATH-MIRROR;
  OCL-DIFF-SVG-PATH-DERIVED for the cycle case). The
  tree set is RenderTree::ALL — one enumeration, no
  skill-prose duplicate (OCL-RENDER-TREE-PARITY).
end note
@enduml
